 {"id":"flywheel_gateway-59c","title":"Comprehensive Notification System","description":"## Background

Effective observability requires proactive alerting when important events occur in the system. Users should not need to constantly monitor dashboards to stay informed about agent status changes, cost anomalies, conflict resolutions, or system issues. A comprehensive notification system bridges this gap by delivering relevant information through the user's preferred channels.

## Problem Statement

Currently, users must manually check the platform to discover issues or important events. This leads to delayed responses to critical situations (agent failures, cost overruns, conflicts requiring approval) and reduces overall platform effectiveness. Different users have different notification preferences - some prefer email digests while others need real-time Slack alerts for urgent issues.

## Technical Approach

### Notification Event Types

```typescript
// apps/gateway/src/types/notification.types.ts

type NotificationCategory = 
  | 'agent'      // Agent lifecycle events
  | 'conflict'   // Conflict detection and resolution
  | 'bead'       // Bead status changes
  | 'cost'       // Cost alerts and anomalies
  | 'system'     // System health and maintenance
  | 'security'   // Security-related events
  | 'team';      // Team and collaboration events

interface NotificationEvent {
  id: string;
  category: NotificationCategory;
  type: NotificationEventType;
  severity: 'info' | 'warning' | 'error' | 'critical';
  title: string;
  message: string;
  data: Record<string, any>; // Event-specific payload
  actorId?: string; // User/agent that triggered event
  targetId?: string; // Affected entity ID
  targetType?: string; // Entity type (agent, bead, etc.)
  orgId: string;
  timestamp: Date;
}

// Agent events
type AgentEventType = 
  | 'agent.created'
  | 'agent.started'
  | 'agent.stopped'
  | 'agent.error'
  | 'agent.recovered'
  | 'agent.rate_limited'
  | 'agent.quota_exceeded'
  | 'agent.config_changed';

// Conflict events
type ConflictEventType =
  | 'conflict.detected'
  | 'conflict.auto_resolved'
  | 'conflict.needs_review'
  | 'conflict.escalated'
  | 'conflict.resolved'
  | 'conflict.timeout';

// Cost events
type CostEventType =
  | 'cost.budget_warning'     // 80% threshold
  | 'cost.budget_critical'    // 95% threshold
  | 'cost.budget_exceeded'
  | 'cost.anomaly_detected'
  | 'cost.daily_summary'
  | 'cost.weekly_report';

// System events
type SystemEventType =
  | 'system.maintenance_scheduled'
  | 'system.maintenance_started'
  | 'system.maintenance_completed'
  | 'system.degraded_performance'
  | 'system.incident_started'
  | 'system.incident_resolved'
  | 'system.update_available';
```

### Multi-Channel Delivery Architecture

```typescript
// apps/gateway/src/services/notification.service.ts

interface NotificationService {
  // Core dispatch
  dispatch(event: NotificationEvent): Promise<void>;
  dispatchBatch(events: NotificationEvent[]): Promise<void>;

  // Channel-specific
  sendInApp(userId: string, notification: Notification): Promise<void>;
  sendEmail(userId: string, notification: Notification): Promise<void>;
  sendSlack(channelConfig: SlackConfig, notification: Notification): Promise<void>;
  sendWebhook(webhookConfig: WebhookConfig, notification: Notification): Promise<void>;

  // Digest management
  queueForDigest(userId: string, notification: Notification): Promise<void>;
  processDigests(frequency: 'daily' | 'weekly'): Promise<void>;
}

// Channel implementations
interface NotificationChannel {
  type: 'in_app' | 'email' | 'slack' | 'webhook';
  enabled: boolean;
  config: ChannelConfig;
  send(notification: FormattedNotification): Promise<DeliveryResult>;
}

interface SlackChannelConfig {
  webhookUrl: string;
  channel?: string; // Override default channel
  username?: string;
  iconEmoji?: string;
  mentionUsers?: string[]; // Slack user IDs for @mentions
  threadTs?: string; // For threaded replies
}

interface WebhookChannelConfig {
  url: string;
  method: 'POST' | 'PUT';
  headers: Record<string, string>;
  authType?: 'none' | 'basic' | 'bearer' | 'hmac';
  authConfig?: AuthConfig;
  retryPolicy: RetryPolicy;
  timeout: number;
}

interface EmailChannelConfig {
  provider: 'sendgrid' | 'ses' | 'smtp';
  fromAddress: string;
  replyTo?: string;
  templates: Map<NotificationEventType, string>;
}
```

### User Notification Preferences

```typescript
// apps/gateway/src/types/preferences.types.ts

interface NotificationPreferences {
  userId: string;
  orgId: string;

  // Global settings
  globalEnabled: boolean;

  // Per-category channel preferences
  categories: {
    [K in NotificationCategory]: CategoryPreference;
  };

  // Quiet hours
  quietHours: {
    enabled: boolean;
